Class JsonHttpClient.Builder, GenericUrl getBaseUrl()

Returns the base URL of the service, for example {@code "https://www.googleapis.com/tasks/v1/"}. Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.

Class JsonHttpClient, String getApplicationName()

Returns the application name to be sent in the User-Agent header of each request or {@code null} for none. Overriding this method is not supported, except for the Google generated libraries for backwards-compatibility reasons. This method will be made final in the 1.7 release.
Class JsonHttpClient, String getBaseUrl()

Returns the base URL of the service, for example {@code "https://www.googleapis.com/tasks/v1/"} . Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.
